commit.message: Fix issues from code review
Rename msgTagger -> subMsg for clarity/consistency

Remove unneeded GoTo msg in CreateSnipbit
- all NoOp/GoTo removed

Sub pages now return top level Cmd BaseMessage.Msg
- Hopefully this allows for more DRY code, more re-usable top level messages
  which can be triggered by the upates/view
CreateBigbit no longer uses Html.map
Create snipbit no longer uses Html.map
Create no longer uses Html.map

Browse no longer uses Html.map
- Should our nested updates return a top level Cmd BaseMessage.Msg? We do otherwise have dup code
DevelopStory no longer uses Html.map
tagMsg -> subMsg for clarity
NewStory no longer uses Html.map
Notifications no longer uses Html.map

ViewProfile no longer uses Html.map
- Weird logout functionality no longer needed, now logout is just a base message
- Add BasePageUtil similar to SubPageUtil
ViewStory no longer uses Html.map
Add need-auth-sign-up-message to ExplanatoryBlurbs module

Remove common message in ViewSnipbit/ViewBigbit
- Added TODO for removing it in ViewStory when Html.map is removed

ViewBigbit no longer uses Html.map
- Removed common NoOp and GoTo

ViewSnipbit page no longer uses Html.map
- Removed common NoOp and GoTo

Welcome page no longer uses Html.map
- Additionally the base GoTo updated to allow clearing shared.apiModalError

commit.message:
Switch to chrome-friendly hotkeys
- The bug with arrow keys seems to only be on firefox, doesn't seem to correspond to anything
  in the code, might just be some firefox textarea bug

Updated to use KK V3.0.0, fixes hotkey buggyness issues
- Seem to have issues though where up/down arrow keys sometimes get disabled
  when using the comment boxes on CreateBigbit/CreateSnipbit. This was ALREADY
  there though before updating to KK V3.0.0, not sure when this started

Closes #26
- The one issue is the usual problem with my KeyboardExtra package and double-clicking keys, same
  problem with shift-tab. Going to fix this in KeyboardExtra so I no longer need to patch it in
  CodeTidbit
